        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 5:45PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 545 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Old Station, or 22 miles north of Chester, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ca 44 At Shasta-Lassen Co Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
